threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered ransomware. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The analyzed binary exhibits clear characteristics of a spyware or Remote Access Trojan (RAT). It employs several high-confidence malicious behaviors, including: 1) Stealthy API resolution via manual LoadLibraryA and GetProcAddress calls to bypass static analysis; 2) Screen capture capabilities found in sub_404255, which uses GDI-like functions (BitBlt logic with SRCCOPY 0xcc0020) to save screenshots as .BMP files; 3) Data exfiltration via HTTP POST requests in sub_4031ee, which utilizes Base64 encoding (IOC: ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/) to package stolen information; 4) System-wide information gathering, including file system traversal, process enumeration, and extensive interaction with the Windows Registry (HKEY_CURRENT_USER) for persistence and data storage.
